37786>>>>>>>// ToDo: Fill in the from-parent child Select view object name for navigate forward
37786>>>>>>>//        WebRegisterPath ntNavigateForward oSelectView
37786>>>>>>>
37786>>>>>>>        Procedure OnRowClick String sRowId
37789>>>>>>>            tWebNavigateData NavigateData
37789>>>>>>>            tWebNavigateData NavigateData
37789>>>>>>>            Get GetNavigateData to NavigateData
37790>>>>>>>
37790>>>>>>>            Case Begin
37790>>>>>>>                Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
37792>>>>>>>                    Send NavigateForward of oZoomEquipo Self
37793>>>>>>>                    Case Break
37794>>>>>>>
37794>>>>>>>                Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
37797>>>>>>>                    Send NavigateClose Self
37798>>>>>>>                    Case Break
37799>>>>>>>
37799>>>>>>>                Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
37802>>>>>>>                    Send NavigateClose Self
37803>>>>>>>                    Case Break
37804>>>>>>>
37804>>>>>>>                Case Else // must be nfUndefined
37804>>>>>>>                    // Respuesta a la pregunta teorica: From main->Select-Zoom, que pasa con InvokingObject?
37804>>>>>>>                    // Al navegar desde el main (Select) hacia un Zoom usando NavigateForward, pasamos 'Self' (el cWebList) 
37804>>>>>>>                    // como InvokingObject. El framework guarda este objeto en la propiedad phoInvokingObject del Zoom destino.
37804>>>>>>>                    // Gracias a esto, cuando se hace un NavigateClose/NavigateBack desde el Zoom, el sistema sabe 
37804>>>>>>>                    // exactamente a que vista y a que control debe devolver el foco y sincronizar el registro activo.
37804>>>>>>>                    Send NavigateForward of oZoomEquipo Self
37805>>>>>>>
37805>>>>>>>            Case End
37805>>>>>>>        End_Procedure
37806>>>>>>>
37806>>>>>>>    End_Object 
